<item>
            <title>[LU-19912] Periodic spurious nfs-related ESTALE</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19912</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a number of reports from the field that NFS servers sometimes complain&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;MDT0000: Cannot find sequence 0x200000001: rc = -2 &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and nfs clients get ESTALE on access randomly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is widely believed is related to lustre sometimes returning invalid parent fid in the form of SEQ_LOCALFILE:REMOTE_PARENT_DIR_OID&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oftentimes reports say that if you do ls in the problematic dir on the lustre client/nfs server node problems go away hinting there&apos;s some cache-related interaction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be good to understand and fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
